activity.title: Gemas medievales de la Toscana: Siena, San Gimignano y Monteriggioni desde Florencia
activity.description:
Cruzando las hermosas colinas de Chianti, llegamos a la joya medieval en lo alto de la colina de MONTERIGGIONI, con sus murallas aún intactas. Aquí podrás empaparte de historia y revivir la atmósfera de tiempos antiguos.

Nuestro tour del día continúa hacia la majestuosa SIENA, famosa por sus espléndidos ejemplos de arquitectura gótica y la tradicional carrera de caballos del Palio. Sigue a tu guía local hasta la sugerente Piazza del Campo, donde se encuentra el magnífico Palazzo Pubblico, con su Torre del Mangia. Visita la Piazza del Duomo y déjate impresionar por la imponente Catedral, una de las más grandes obras del gótico italiano. Antes de salir de Siena, tendrás tiempo libre para explorar su centro histórico a tu propio ritmo.

A continuación, nos dirigimos a SAN GIMIGNANO, famosa por su vino blanco, la mundialmente conocida Vernaccia, y sus rascacielos, ¡también declarados Patrimonio de la Humanidad por la UNESCO! La visita es libre para hacer turismo independiente, paseando por las estrechas calles y admirando el paisaje relajante.

Al final del recorrido del día, nos trasladamos a la zona de CHIANTI, con sus paisajes dignos de una postal. Tendrás la oportunidad de degustar el mejor vino tinto Chianti en una finca vinícola rústica, junto con aperitivos caseros y una degustación de vinos y aceite.

tripadvisorReview.name: Medieval Gems of Tuscany: Siena, San Gimignano and Monteriggioni
tripadvisorReview.description: Combine medieval gems, fine wines, and UNESCO-listed monuments on this full-day tour of central Tuscany from Florence. Marvel over the medieval castle of Monteriggioni; explore the architectural wonders of historic Siena; and admire the striking skyline of hilltop San Gimignano. Finish your tour with a wine tasting at a local winery in the Chianti region.

agendaItems.title: Florence
agendaItems.body: There is no time to waste when exploring the stunning Tuscany hills! Meet your tour guide at Piazzale Montelungo Bus Terminal early in the morning. Piazzale Montelungo is located 5-10 minutes walking distance from the Santa Maria Novella train station. Hop on the comfortable coach bus, choose your seat, and relax before departing on your journey! The drive to Monteriggioni will take about one hour. During the journey, your guide will entertain you with plenty of interesting information about Tuscany and its sights on the way. Upon arrival, your expert guide will share some interesting information and fun stories about Monteriggioni! If you have any questions, your guide will be there to assist you.

agendaItems.title: Monteriggioni, Province of Siena
agendaItems.body: You will have one hour of free time to explore Monteriggioni, Tuscany's hidden gem. This town is encompassed by its stunning, medieval walls. The town itself is so well preserved, you will feel as though you have travelled back in time to the Renaissance era... Explore the small cobblestone alleyways, take in the lovely views, and enjoy a cappuccino in the essence of historic Tuscany.

agendaItems.title: Siena
agendaItems.body: Next, you will head to a truly unique, medieval city in Tuscany - Siena! The drive will take about thirty minutes, and then your guide will lead you through the picturesque, ancient streets in the heart of the city until you reach Piazza del Campo. In the largest square of the city, you will meet a local and professional city guide for your included walking tour of Siena. For about an hour, the guide will share fascinating facts about this incredible city (which is listed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site), and you will visit some of the most famous points of interest. The end of the walking tour will lead you to the Siena Cathedral, where you can enter at your own expense to see the breathtaking decorations and unique architecture.

agendaItems.title: Piazza del Campo, Siena
agendaItems.body: Your walking tour will begin in Piazza del Campo, a fascinating, oval-shaped piazza in the center of Siena. Not only is this a popular spot for locals to meet up with friends and relax, but it is also home to a historic palio horse race! Every year, the different neighborhoods of Siena join for the epic and exciting horse race. Your guide will share plenty of local stories as you walk throughout the Piazza and see some of the famous monuments. Your professional guide will share information in a way which brings the history of the city to life, in a vivid, storytelling manner.

agendaItems.title: Siena's Cathedral (Duomo)
agendaItems.body: Your walking tour ends in front of the iconic Duomo of Siena. This absolutely stunning piece of architecture is equally as beautiful inside as outside; if you would like to enter the cathedral, you will have some free time to do so (ticket is not included). If you prefer to explore the city in your free time after the walking tour, there will be some time for independent sightseeing. One of the most beautiful Gothic-style churches in Italy, with its radiant green and white marble decorations

agendaItems.title: San Gimignano, province of Siena
agendaItems.body: Your journey through Tuscany will continue to San Gimignano, known as the "town of towers," because of its fascinating medieval towers still perfectly intact. The drive will take about an hour, and you will see the stunning "medieval skyscrapers" from a distance as your bus pulls into the historic town. Your guide will lead you past an incredible panoramic viewpoint of the Tuscan hills, then through the ancient city doors. You will have an hour to independently explore the town - walk the picturesque alleyways, visit the Duomo, or climb the tallest tower!

agendaItems.title: Chianti Wine Region
agendaItems.body: After exploring these medieval Tuscan cities, you will undoubtedly be ready for some Tuscan wine! Meet back with your group, and head to a nearby wine estate in the countryside outside of San Gimignano. In about fifteen minutes, you will arrive at this characteristic wine estate, where you will be seated in a modern and beautiful tasting room built into the cellar. Enjoy the delicious wine produced at the estate: during the wine tasting, the wine producer will share the secrets of Chianti wine production with your group. At the end of the wine tasting, you will have the opportunity to purchase bottles as a high-quality souvenir of your incredible day in Tuscany!

agendaItems.title: Piazzale Montelungo, Florence
agendaItems.body: End your journey through Tuscany with unforgettable views of the Tuscan hills as the sunsets. The drive will take about an hour, and you will arrive in Florence in early evening.
